    "docHtml": "<p>A curved iron blade hafted short on a handle, the sickle is first a harvest tool, second a weapon. Farmers and peasant-levies swing it to cut grain and flesh alike, effective against the lightly armored or unarmoured. Its curve favors slashing over thrusting; it catches on shield rims and garrottes at close work. Common among irregular troops lacking coin for proper arms.</p>\n",
